            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="707" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d707">
                <head>No. 705.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram from secretary of state,
                                    Madrid, to Spanish minister, Washington. Received November 28,
                                    1873, 9.15 a.m.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1873-11-28" notBefore="1873-11-12">undated</date>].</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Negotiations renewed in Madrid. Confer again with Mr. Fish on the
                                basis of the last official note, [official telegram ?] and renew to
                                him the assurances of the good faith and rectitude of our
                                proposition; assuring him likewise that our agreement, whatever it
                                may be, shall be beyond all doubt carried out in Cuba.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
